embedMessage.title: %s Setup Configuration
embedMessage.description:
Thanks for adding me to your server! Before you start, I need to setup a few things. I can do two configurations:

**üñ•Ô∏è Automatic Setup** *(Recommended)*
This will create a new channel category with the relevant channels so that your members can generate voice channels with ease. This will also have a text channel so that your members can manage their channels.

**‚öôÔ∏è Manual Setup**
If you already have a category setup with a text and voice channel, I can use them with this setup. I will ask for category and channel IDs so that I know which category you want me to control.

embedMessage.title: %s Setup Repair
embedMessage.description:
Welcome to Setup Repair mode, you have two options here, you can attempt a repair of the current configuration, or reset the entire configuration.

**NOTICE:** Resetting the configuration will not remove any channels, this will only reset the configuration to the default out of the box state, allowing you to gather any information in previously created channels.

**üîß Repair Setup**
If you have already setup your server, you can use this option to attempt a repair of the intended configuration, said option will seek to:

**o** Find any channels that have been removed
**o** Attempt to move channels back into there respective category.

If this is unsuccessful, you'll be notified that this was the case, and you can try alternative option.

**üîÑ Reset Setup**
Perform a partial reset of the Guild Database file, this will remove any data pertaining to the channels of this Guild.

By performing this reset option, you could be effecting the following operations:

**o** Blacklisted Member(s)
**o** Lockdown Status
**o** Member(s) currently using the system.

This will not effect the Permission system, Disabled Commands or SetCommandChannel.

embedMessageRepair.title: Setup Repair Complete!
embedMessageRepair.description:
The Repair operation completed successfully. You may use the system as normal!

If the problem still persists, please try running the setup again and try the reset option.

embedMessageReset.description: The Reset operation completed successfully. **You may now run setup again!**

embedNewMemberMessage.title: Hello! I'm excited to see you're using our new Voice Channel System!
embedNewMemberMessage.description:
Keep in mind that this system is in an beta state, and if you run into any issues, please message a member of staff on the server.

**What is this?**
**-** Use this system to automatically create your own voice channel - the system will also move you into said voice channel.
**-** If you don't want to create a voice channel, feel free to join other member created voice channels. Have fun!

**How to manage a channel**
By default, you are only allowed to type commands in the provided #commands text channel (This is located directly above the "Join to Create Channel")

In order to kick a member from your channel, use the command:

%skick [@Mention]

For example: %skick @Huskies

For further command assistance type: %shelp

Also keep in mind that there is a 20 second cool-down for creating a voice channel. This is to avoid abuse of the voice system.

*Please note that any commands can be disabled by a member of staff, and they reserve the right to disable any commands and deny access to this system without notice.*
